6:
Wow... Rudy took out every one of
them by herself.
14:
Ah, yes. I'm running an older OS, but I
am fully equipped with battle
functions and aim assist.
19:
Battle functions, huh? Reminds me
of that Administrator of yours.
20:
You, uh... You know the Administrator
isn't around anymore, right?
22:
Yes. I was indisposed at the time,
but I received reports of the incident.
25:
Then what's keepin' you? You could
go home.
28:
Must I? I am afraid I do not
understand the question. Do you
mean that I do not belong in this
world?
35:
He means that, with the evil
defeated, you should be safe if you
return.
46:
We can continue this later.
Something is watching us.
54:
Get into formation! It's coming right
for us!
57:
What are you doing, Rudy?! That's
dangerous!
61:
I don't mind. I am meant to be used
to the fullest extent of my abilities.
81: I'm fine. Don't worry about me.
103:
You don't seem to be in high spirits.
What's wrong?
105:
Due to earlier events, everyone gave
me quite the scolding.
107: And what did they scold you for?
109:
I am a disposable model, designed
for ease of recyclability, but... The
others were upset that I overclocked
my systems to help them.
114:
I would be very sad if I never saw
you again.
116:
But a tool should be used until it
cannot be used anymore, and only
my combat functions are
operational.
121: I don't see you as a tool.
123: Then what am I to you?
138:
You consider me a friend. Maybe I
am more defective than I thought.
144:
When I recovered from being a bug,
I was told that a hole remained in
my memory.
145:
This is why I cannot experience the
sensations and emotions that you
and everyone else share.
151:
So you're unique. There's nothing
wrong with that.
153:
Even though I'm fundamentally
different than you?
156:
No one said that had to be a bad
thing.
169:
I just realized... I don't know even why
I thought being different was a bad
thing.
172:
You see? What matters to me is that
you come home at the end of the
day.
175:
How fascinating... What is it that
drives you and everyone else? What
is it that drives me?
